Using a Loop to Access All Elements

When dealing with arrays, it's common to use a loop (like for or
while) to iterate through all elements and access or modify them.

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {

int numbers[5] = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50}; // Array declaration and initialization

// Loop to access and print all elements

for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {

printf("Element at index %d: %d\n", i, numbers[i]);

}

return 0;
}
// output
Element at index 0: 10

Element at index 1: 20

Element at index 2: 30

Element at index 3: 40

Element at index 4: 50
